    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Late Roman and Byzantine pierced metalwork technique performed upon a soft metal such as gold using a drill and chisel to produce arabesques and other lacey ornamental designs.</Note_Text>
